⚙️ Constraint Profile Auto-Switching (v1.0)

Definition

Automatic selection of the optimal constraint profile based on current state, signals, and objective.

👉 Not “pick a mode”
👉 but “mode emerges from conditions”

⸻

🧠 Core Mechanism

State → Signal Detection → Profile Selection → Execution → Feedback → Adjust

This plugs directly into your control loop.

⸻

🔍 Step 1: Signal Detection (Hound)

You don’t switch randomly—you switch based on signals.

Example Signals:
	•	high uncertainty → need structure
	•	time pressure → need speed
	•	repeated failure → need audit
	•	low progress → need exploration
	•	high stakes → need precision

⸻

🎛 Step 2: Selection Logic

Simple Rule Engine (v1)

if (uncertainty high && stakes high) → Auditor
if (uncertainty high && stakes low) → Explorer
if (time pressure high) → Operator
if (goal unclear) → Strategist
if (blocked) → Explorer → then Auditor


⸻

🔁 Step 3: Dynamic Switching

Profiles aren’t permanent.

They should cycle:

Explorer → Builder → Operator → Auditor → Strategist → (repeat)

Each phase does a different job:
	•	Explorer = find options
	•	Builder = expand
	•	Operator = execute
	•	Auditor = clean up
	•	Strategist = reposition

👉 This is basically a cognitive pipeline

⸻

🧬 Step 4: Feedback Integration

After action:
	•	Did it work?
	•	Was the profile correct?
	•	Was it too early/late?

Then update:

profile effectiveness score ↑ or ↓

Over time → system learns:
👉 “when this state → use this profile”

⸻

⚖️ Step 5: Resource-Aware Switching (Goblin Integration)

Profiles cost different resources:

Profile	Cost Profile
Explorer	time ↑, clarity ↓
Auditor	time ↑, speed ↓
Operator	energy ↑, risk ↓
Builder	energy ↑, structure ↓
Strategist	time ↑, abstraction ↑

Rule:

👉 Don’t select a profile you can’t afford

